search:Advanced Error Handling in React-.content:
- Ensure Firebase SDK is up to date using `npm install @react-native-firebase/app@latest`.
- For iOS, make sure the bundle identifier matches your Firebase project settings.
- On Android, check that SHA-1 and SHA-256 fingerprints are correctly configured in Firebase console under Project Settings > General > Your apps.
- For Apple authentication on iOS, use `@invertase/react-native-apple-authentication` for handling sign-in with Apple.
- Implement error handling using try-catch blocks around authentication methods to catch and log errors effectively.
- Example of handling Firebase login errors:
  ```javascript
  import auth from '@react-native-firebase/auth';

  async function signIn(email, password) {
    try {
      await auth().signInWithEmailAndPassword(email, password);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Authentication failed:', error.message);
    }
  }
  ```
- Ensure all necessary permissions are granted in `Info.plist` for iOS and `AndroidManifest.xml` for Android.
- For debugging, use Firebase Authentication debug tokens to verify authentication requests.
